The mental health advisory committee of each county shall consist of:
As nonvoting ex officio members, the following individuals or their designees:
The health officer for the county;
A representative of a State inpatient facility that serves that county, appointed as provided in paragraph (2) of this subsection;
The county mental health director;
The director of the core service agency, if any; and
In jurisdictions with designated State inpatient beds located in local general hospitals, a representative from that facility; and
As voting members, appointed by the governing body of the county and representative of the county's major socio-economic and ethnic groups:
At least 5, but not more than 7, representatives selected from among the following groups or agencies:
At least 5 individuals selected from among the following groups or organizations and appointed as provided in paragraph (3) of this subsection:
